* Required Fields: This option defines how many days the transaction remains open after authorization. A value of 0 means that the authorization is captured as soon as possible. We recommend you to define a cron job in your shop especially if the capture delay is greater than 0 in order to automatically update the transaction status. How this can be done is described in the latest version of the integration manual. Please check with BNP Paribas Mercanet which delay is possible and what implication a delay may have.

Customweb_BNPMercanetCw::* Required Fiel: Customweb_BNPMercanetCw::When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of BNP Paribas Mercanet is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.
* Required Fields: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of BNP Paribas Mercanet is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.
